verbose_text: In fact, a Cochrane meta-analysis of randomized double-blind active- or placebo controlled trials in acute musculoskeletal pain concluded that there is moderate- to high-quality evidence that topical diclofenac, ibuprofen, ketoprofen, piroxicam, and indomethacin all produce superior PR compared with topical placebo in acute conditions including strains, sprains, and other types of sports or overuse related injuries, with diclofenac and ketoprofen being the most effective.
evidence: ibuprofen, ketoprofen, piroxicam, and indomethacin all produce superior PR
